    <div class="post-txt">
    <p></p><p><strong>Siberian&nbsp;State Medical University&nbsp;trains the next generation of doctors by performing high quality medical research and by offering excellent education.</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Established in 1878,&nbsp;<strong>Siberian State Medical University</strong>&nbsp;is one of the most well-known and highly reputable medical schools in Russia owing to its top caliber academic and scientific body, and experienced physicians and professors.</p>
<p>Among the graduates are two presidents of the Russian Academy of Medical Sciences, 25 associate members of the Russian Academy of Medical Sciences, 42 academicians.</p>
<p><strong>Siberian State Medical University</strong><strong>‘</strong><strong>s </strong>core mission is to advance patient care and public health in the Russian Federation through teaching, research and clinical excellence.</p>
<p>The University aims at improving the quality of life and health of the population through innovation in education, research and patient care offering top-quality training, educational and research opportunities to the students.</p>
<p>Whether you are interested in a career in healthcare as a doctor/physician or as a scientist exploring clinical investigation and research,&nbsp;<strong>Siberian State Medical University</strong>&nbsp;has what you are looking for. <strong>Siberian State Medical University</strong><strong>‘</strong><strong>s </strong>medical and graduate programs are ranked among the top in the nation and the academic faculty, scientists, and healthcare professionals are best experts in their fields.</p>
<h4 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>UNDERGRADUATE PROGRAMS</strong></span></h4>
<p>For the first 3 years of training students are mainly focused on theoretical subjects at the departments of biology, medical physics, chemistry, biochemistry, human anatomy, histology, physiology, pathology, microbiology, Latin and foreign languages, social sciences. During the last 3.5 years students are offered extensive practical training in various fields of&nbsp;internal medicine, surgery, obstetrics and gynecology, public health and prevention. One of the most distinguished features of our medical education is complete practical student-patient experience in all clinical classes. This provides a unique opportunity for students to be well skilled in modern diagnostic and treatment approaches.</p>
<p>Development of research skills based on modern methodology and up-to-date equipment is another important part of the program. All divisions of the department&nbsp;provide facilities for students to be involved in research under the guidance of the advisors from the Faculty.</p>
<h5><strong><span style="color: #333399;">MEDICAL FACULTY</span></strong></h5>
<p>The Department of General Medicine is the university’s oldest department. It consists of 29 theoretical and clinical divisions. The duration of study is 6 years.</p>
<p>Medical Faculty is currently not only the leader in the Siberian State Medical University, but also the largest among the faculties of all universities in Tomsk considering the number of doctors, candidates of sciences, members of state academies and departments. Throughout its history, the faculty has prepared more than 20 thousand. Doctors. Graduates work in all regions of Russia, the CIS republics, in more than 30 countries – Germany, Norway, Israel, USA, Canada, Australia and achieve high results.&nbsp;</p>
<h5><strong><span style="color: #333399;">PEDIATRICS FACULTY</span></strong></h5>
<p>At the Faculty of extensive clinical base – own children’s clinic and the department, located at the base of major institutions, such as the Regional Children’s Hospital and Regional Perinatal Center. The graduates successfully work in health – care institutions, clinical centers and medical schools in all regions of Russia, CIS and far abroad. Most importantly, the pediatric faculty applicants are aiming to work exactly with children, so there is always a special spirit in the faculty, we can say “pediatric brotherhood.” Small contingent of students allows you to organize the educational process in many ways individually. This contributes to better learning of theoretical knowledge, the successful development of practical skills.</p>
<p>Pediatric Faculty of SSMU opened in 1944. For more than 70 years of history here were&nbsp;trained about 11 000 experts, who are daily in children’s clinics, hospitals, maternity hospitals and perinatal centers save thousands of children’s lives, conduct transactions and advice to their young patients and their parents. Pediatrician – the most responsible and difficult profession in the consulting business, because to approach the child can only caring and sociable people. Pediatrician engaged in the prevention, diagnosis and treatment of diseases in children and adolescents (from birth to 18 years).</p>
<h5><strong><span style="color: #333399;">PHARMACY FACULTY</span></strong></h5>
<p>At the disposal of the departments of the Faculty of the major production bases for practical training – a branch of scientific-production association “Microgen” in Tomsk “Virion”, Tomsk innovative company “Artlife” training laboratory in the company “Astrafarm” study pharmacy – the oldest pharmacy in Tomsk Governorate Tomsk regional pharmacy warehouse. Already during their studies, students have the opportunity to develop and produce a pilot batch of pharmaceutical products in the center of SSMU introduction of technology where today 3 clinical trials of the drug, developed at the Faculty of Pharmacy.</p>
<p>As part of the Siberian State Medical University in 1941, operates the first in Siberia and the Far East, Faculty of Pharmacy, today it is a leading center for training pharmacists Russia. More than 8000 specialists have graduated here, among them 200 doctors and candidates of sciences.</p>
<h5><strong><span style="color: #333399;">BIOLOGICAL FACULTY</span></strong></h5>
<p>Medical Biochemistry examines the chemical processes in the body that determine all aspects of human life, these studies are the basis for the development of new areas of medical science. Along with access to fundamental knowledge students master the most sophisticated methods of biochemical research. Doctors biochemists demand in research centers throughout Russia, work in practical public health physicians in clinical laboratory diagnostics, doctors of Forensic Medicine, virologists, geneticists, heads of biochemical and clinical laboratories. Graduates work at the Institute for Human Gene Therapy, Harvard, Vanderbilt, Stanford University in the US, the Institute of Biochemistry at the Max Planck in Germany and many others.</p>
<p>Faculty opened in 1975 and is the only one in the Urals, the training of personnel for research institutes of medical and biological and medical fields. Training involves a combination of scientific disciplines fundamental to clinical medicine. Faculty trains professional scientists: every fifth graduate is a doctor or a PhD. A distinctive feature of the training is to a large amount of independent work, the emphasis on the scientific activities of students, they receive practical skills of researchers. Having fundamental training, our graduates have a unique experience, knowledge and ability to implement them in practical healthcare.</p>
<p>Graduates of the ICF after graduation can enter a PhD program. They work as research associates in research institutes, university professors, as well as in practical public health by laboratory, functional, radiotherapy and ultrasound diagnostics physicians. In addition to Russia, our graduates work in their specialties in the CIS countries, the USA, Germany, France, Belgium, South Korea, Israel, Canada, Sweden, Slovenia, the Czech Republic, etc.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h4 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>POSTGRADUATE PROGRAMS</strong></span></h4>
<p>The Department of Professional Development and Retraining is one of the largest centers of additional professional education in the Russian Federation, it comprises 11 departments and 9 courses where 77 specialties are available for further training.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The faculty provides courses to raise the level of skills in all directions of training specialists at&nbsp;<strong>SSMU</strong>.</p>
<p>Classes are conducted by highly qualified teachers (professors, associate professors, doctors and candidates of medical sciences). Upon graduation students are rewarded standard form documents (certificates of vocational retraining, professional certificates and certificates of advanced training).&nbsp;</p>
